text.section:
The driver of a vehicle may not stop, stand, or park the vehicle on any Authority highway, except:
If necessary to avoid injury or damage to any person or property;
In compliance with the lawful direction of an authorized employee of the Authority highway;
At a designated area for the transaction of business at an Administration building; or
If the vehicle is disabled or involved in an accident, in which case the vehicle shall be moved, if possible:
To the shoulder of the roadway;
Adjacent to the emergency walkway on a bridge; or
As otherwise directed by a patrol officer.
